需求描述

这个图10D可以实现吗？真的很漂亮，蝴蝶图 | Can this Figure 10D be implemented? It’s really beautiful, butterfly plot

From https://www.thno.org/v11p3089.htm

Figure 6. Roles of Siglec15 in predicting immune phenotypes in the XiangYing cohort. (C) Correlations between Siglec15 and the steps of the cancer immunity cycle. (D) Correlations between Siglec15 and the enrichment scores of immunotherapy-predicted pathways.

图的解析

  • 用热图展示通路的自相关分析结果；
  • C和D两个热图，分别展示两类通路各自的相关分析结果，放在一起方便对比；
  • 用连线展示Siglec15跟两类通路的各个具体通路之间的相关性，实线代表正相关、虚线代表负相关，用颜色代表P value；

应用场景 | Application Scenario

展示相关性分析结果，多对多（C热图、D热图）、1对多（Siglec15跟C的连线，Siglec15跟D的连线）、两组对比（C和D画一起）画一起。

例文是1个基因跟多个通路的相关性，可以替换为1个基因跟多个基因之间、或1个通路跟多个基因之间等等，灵活套用。

如果只有一组，就是单独的C或D；如果有两组，就像例文一样拼成蝴蝶；如果有更多组，同样套用easy_input*文件，画出多个图后，按自己的审美组合。

Display correlation analysis results, many-to-many (C heatmap, D heatmap), one-to-many (Siglec15 connections with C, Siglec15 connections with D), two-group comparison (C and D plotted together).

The example shows correlations between 1 gene and multiple pathways, which can be replaced with correlations between 1 gene and multiple genes, or 1 pathway and multiple genes, etc., for flexible application.

If there is only one group, it’s a separate C or D; if there are two groups, combine them like a butterfly as in the example; if there are more groups, apply the same easy_input* files, create multiple plots, and combine them according to your aesthetic preferences.

自定义函数（来自cogena），用于提取msigdb特定通路的基因，参考FigureYa151pathifier

Custom function (from cogena) for extracting genes of specific pathways from msigdb, reference FigureYa151pathifier

# 读取gmt文件为列表形式，满足pathifier的输入要求
# Read gmt file as list format to meet pathifier input requirements

gmt2list <- function(annofile){
  if (!file.exists(annofile)) {
    stop("There is no such gmt file.")
  }
  
  if (tools::file_ext(annofile) == "xz") {
    annofile <- xzfile(annofile)
    x <- scan(annofile, what="", sep="\n", quiet=TRUE)
    close(annofile)
  } else if (tools::file_ext(annofile) == "gmt") {
    x <- scan(annofile, what="", sep="\n", quiet=TRUE)
  } else {
    stop ("Only gmt and gmt.xz are accepted for gmt2list")
  }
  
  y <- strsplit(x, "\t")
  names(y) <- sapply(y, `[[`, 1)
  
  annoList <- lapply(y, `[`, c(-1,-2))
  return(annoList)
}

输入文件的获得 | Obtaining Input Files

如果你的数据已经整理为easy_input_*.txt的格式，就可以直接进入“开始画图”。

下面用基因表达矩阵和通路-基因信息，计算各通路的富集得分（可以理解为通路的表达矩阵）。

  • tcga_blca_fpkm.txt，基因表达矩阵。
  • 通路的基因信息，例文根据文献整理了两类通路，其他通路套用这样的格式即可：
    • bladder cancer signature.txt，膀胱癌相关签名，每行一个通路，第一列为通路名（Signature），第二列为基因（Genes）。用于绘制(C) Correlations between Siglec15 and the steps of the cancer immunity cycle。出自例文的Table S9.xlsx，Bladder cancer signatures，取Signature和Genes两列。是例文作者从这篇文章整理出来的：Mariathasan S, Turley SJ, Nickles D, Castiglioni A, Yuen K, Wang Y, et al. TGFβ attenuates tumour response to PD-L1 blockade by contributing to exclusion of T cells. Nature. 2018; 554: 544-8.
    • immunotherapy predicted pathways.txt，治疗签名，用于绘制(D) Correlations between Siglec15 and the enrichment scores of immunotherapy-predicted pathways。整理自例文的Table S9.xlsx，Therapeutic predicted pathways，选取Description一列为Anticancer_immunotherapy的Pathway及其对应的Genes。可以直接拿来用到自己的文章里，记得引用例文哦～～

If your data is already formatted as easy_input_*.txt, you can directly proceed to “Start Plotting”.

Below, using gene expression matrix and pathway-gene information, calculate the enrichment scores for each pathway (can be understood as pathway expression matrix).

  • tcga_blca_fpkm.txt, gene expression matrix.
  • Pathway gene information: The example paper organized two types of pathways based on literature, other pathways can follow this format:
    • bladder cancer signature.txt, bladder cancer-related signatures, with one pathway per row, first column as pathway name (Signature), second column as genes (Genes). Used for plotting (C) Correlations between Siglec15 and the steps of the cancer immunity cycle. Derived from Table S9.xlsx of the example paper, Bladder cancer signatures, taking Signature and Genes columns. Organized by the example paper authors from this article: Mariathasan S, Turley SJ, Nickles D, Castiglioni A, Yuen K, Wang Y, et al. TGFβ attenuates tumour response to PD-L1 blockade by contributing to exclusion of T cells. Nature. 2018; 554: 544-8.
    • immunotherapy predicted pathways.txt, therapeutic signatures, used for plotting (D) Correlations between Siglec15 and the enrichment scores of immunotherapy-predicted pathways. Organized from Table S9.xlsx of the example paper, Therapeutic predicted pathways, selecting Pathways with Description as Anticancer_immunotherapy and their corresponding Genes. Can be directly used in your own article, remember to cite the example paper~~

“A set of gene signatures positively correlated with the clinical response of an anti-PD-L1 agent (atezolizumab) in BLCA were collected from Mariathasan’s study [27]. Twelve bladder cancer signatures that are specific to different molecular subtypes were collected from the study performed by the Bladder Cancer Molecular Taxonomy Group [19]. We also collected other therapeutic signatures, including oncogenic pathways that could shape a non-inflamed TME, targeted therapy-associated gene signatures, and gene signatures predicting radiotherapy responses (Table S9).”

# 读取数据 | Load data
tryCatch({
  expr <- fread("tcga_blca_fpkm.txt", sep = "\t", header = TRUE, check.names = FALSE)
  expr <- as.data.frame(expr)
  rownames(expr) <- expr[, 1]
  expr <- expr[, -1]
  
  # 检查SIGLEC15基因是否存在 | Detect SIGLEC15
  if (!"SIGLEC15" %in% rownames(expr)) {
    stop("SIGLEC15 gene not found in expression matrix")
  }
  
  # 提取肿瘤样本 | Extract tumor samples
  tumsam <- colnames(expr)[substr(colnames(expr), 11, 13) == "01A"]
  
  if (length(tumsam) == 0) {
    stop("No tumor samples found")
  }
  
  # 取出SIGLEC15表达量 | Extract SIGLEC15 expression
  siglec15 <- log2(expr["SIGLEC15",tumsam] + 1)
  write.csv(siglec15, "easy_input_gene.csv")
  
  cat("数据加载成功，找到", length(tumsam), "个肿瘤样本\n")
  
}, error = function(e) {
  cat("数据加载错误:", e$message, "\n")
  stop(e)
})
## 数据加载成功，找到 307 个肿瘤样本
# load immunotherapy-predicted pathways
immPath <- read.table("immunotherapy predicted pathways.txt",sep = "\t",row.names = 1,check.names = F,stringsAsFactors = F,header = T)
immPath.list <- list()
for (i in rownames(immPath)) {
  tmp <- immPath[i,"Genes"]
  tmp <- toupper(unlist(strsplit(tmp,", ",fixed = T)))
  tmp <- gsub(" ","",tmp)
  immPath.list[[i]] <- tmp
}

# 加载膀胱癌相关签名 | Load bladder cancer related signatures
blcaPath <- read.table("bladder cancer signature.txt",sep = "\t",row.names = 1,check.names = F,stringsAsFactors = F,header = T)
blcaPath.list <- list()
for (i in rownames(blcaPath)) {
  tmp <- blcaPath[i,"Genes"]
  tmp <- toupper(unlist(strsplit(tmp,", ",fixed = T)))
  tmp <- gsub(" ","",tmp)
  blcaPath.list[[i]] <- tmp
}

计算富集得分，保存到文件，便于套用

Calculate enrichment scores, save to files for easy reuse

# 计算immunotherapy-predicted pathways的富集得分
# Calculate enrichment scores for immunotherapy-predicted pathways
immPath.param <- GSVA::ssgseaParam(
  as.matrix(log2(expr[,tumsam] + 1)),
  immPath.list
)
immPath.score <- GSVA::gsva(immPath.param, verbose = FALSE)
## ! 694 genes with constant values throughout the samples
# 保存到文件，便于套用 | Save to file for easy reuse
write.table(immPath.score, "easy_input_immPath.txt", sep = "\t", row.names = TRUE, col.names = NA, quote = FALSE)

# 计算膀胱癌相关签名的富集得分
# Calculate enrichment scores for bladder cancer related signatures
blcaPath.param <- GSVA::ssgseaParam(
  as.matrix(log2(expr[,tumsam] + 1)),
  blcaPath.list
)
blcaPath.score <- GSVA::gsva(blcaPath.param, verbose = FALSE)
## ! 694 genes with constant values throughout the samples
## ! Duplicated gene IDs removed from gene set Basal_differentiation
## ! Duplicated gene IDs removed from gene set Smooth_muscle
# 保存到文件，便于套用 | Save to file for easy reuse
write.table(blcaPath.score, "easy_input_blcaPath.txt", sep = "\t", row.names = TRUE, col.names = NA, quote = FALSE)

对于自己的数据，你可能想提取自己感兴趣的通路计算通路的富集得分。可以从msigdb下载gmt文件c5.all.v7.4.symbols.gmt，提取自己感兴趣的通路及其对应的基因，计算富集得分。

For your own data, you may want to extract pathways of interest and calculate their enrichment scores. You can download the gmt file c5.all.v7.4.symbols.gmt from msigdb, extract pathways of interest and their corresponding genes, and calculate enrichment scores.

# 从gmt文件提取感兴趣的通路 | Extract pathways of interest from gmt file
# 例如提取带有`METABOLISM`字样的通路 | For example, extract pathways containing `METABOLISM`
gset <- gmt2list("c5.all.v7.4.symbols.gmt") 

# 使用data.table的%like%操作符提取包含METABOLISM的通路
# Use data.table's %like% operator to extract pathways containing METABOLISM
gset.list <- gset[names(gset) %like% "METABOLISM"]

# 检查基因集是否为空
if (length(gset.list) == 0) {
  stop("No pathways found containing 'METABOLISM'. Please check your gmt file and filter criteria.")
}

cat("Found", length(gset.list), "pathways containing 'METABOLISM'\n")

# 计算通路富集得分 | Calculate pathway enrichment scores
gset.score <- GSVA::gsva(
  expr = as.matrix(log2(expr[, tumsam] + 1)),
  gset.idx.list = gset.list,
  method = "ssgsea",
  verbose = FALSE,  # 减少输出信息
  parallel.sz = 1   # 单线程运行，避免并行问题
)

# 保存到文件 | Save to file
write.table(gset.score, "easy_input_gset.txt", sep = "\t", row.names = TRUE, col.names = NA, quote = FALSE)

cat("Pathway enrichment scores saved to 'easy_input_gset.txt'\n")

开始画图 ｜ Start Plotting

关于 -log10(p-value) 的使用说明 | About -log10(p-value) Usage

本图使用 -log10(p-value) 来可视化显著性水平，这是生物信息学中的标准做法。数值越大表示显著性越强：

  • 连线颜色基于 -log10(p-value) 进行编码
  • 图例中同时显示 p-value 范围和对应的 -log10(p-value) 范围
  • 参考：https://mp.weixin.qq.com/s/dyaeBr8tnJhxN-fuYjE-hQ

This plot uses -log10(p-value) to visualize significance levels, which is a standard practice in bioinformatics. Higher values indicate stronger significance:

  • Line colors are encoded based on -log10(p-value)
  • The legend displays both p-value ranges and corresponding -log10(p-value) ranges
  • Reference: https://mp.weixin.qq.com/s/dyaeBr8tnJhxN-fuYjE-hQ
# 加载单个基因的表达量，也就是"1对多"的"1"
# Load expression of a single gene, which is the "1" in "1-to-many"
siglec15 <- read.csv("easy_input_gene.csv", row.names = 1, check.names = F)

# 加载第一组富集得分 | Load first set of enrichment scores
immPath.score <- read.table("easy_input_immPath.txt", check.names = F)
# 跟目标基因SIGLEC15的表达量合并 | Merge with target gene SIGLEC15 expression
immPath.score <- rbind.data.frame(immPath.score,
                                  siglec15)

# 加载第二组富集得分 | Load second set of enrichment scores
blcaPath.score <- read.table("easy_input_blcaPath.txt", check.names = F)
# 跟目标基因SIGLEC15的表达量合并 | Merge with target gene SIGLEC15 expression
blcaPath.score <- rbind.data.frame(blcaPath.score,
                                   siglec15)

循环计算相关性并画图 | Loop to calculate correlations and plot

# 循环计算相关性并绘制左下角
immCorSiglec15 <- NULL
for (i in rownames(immPath.score)) {
  # 确保数据是数值型
  x_data <- as.numeric(immPath.score[i,])
  y_data <- as.numeric(siglec15)
  
  # 检查数据是否有效
  if (any(is.na(x_data)) || any(is.na(y_data))) {
    cat("警告: 数据中包含NA值，跳过", i, "\n")
    next
  }
  
  cr <- cor.test(x_data, y_data, method = "pearson")
  immCorSiglec15 <- rbind.data.frame(immCorSiglec15,
                                     data.frame(gene = "Siglec15",
                                                path = i,
                                                r = cr$estimate,
                                                p = cr$p.value,
                                                stringsAsFactors = F),
                                     stringsAsFactors = F)
}
immCorSiglec15$sign <- ifelse(immCorSiglec15$r > 0,"pos","neg")
immCorSiglec15$absR <- abs(immCorSiglec15$r)
immCorSiglec15$rSeg <- as.character(cut(immCorSiglec15$absR,c(0,0.25,0.5,0.75,1),labels = c("0.25","0.50","0.75","1.00"),include.lowest = T))
immCorSiglec15$pSeg <- as.character(cut(-log10(immCorSiglec15$p),c(0,2,5,10,Inf),labels = c("ns (p≥0.01)","<0.01 (2≤-log10p<5)","<0.001 (5≤-log10p<10)","<1e-10 (-log10p≥10)"),include.lowest = T))
immCorSiglec15[nrow(immCorSiglec15),"pSeg"] <- "Not Applicable"

immCorSiglec15$rSeg <- factor(immCorSiglec15$rSeg, levels = c("0.25","0.50","0.75","1.00"))
immCorSiglec15$pSeg <- factor(immCorSiglec15$pSeg, levels = c("<1e-10 (-log10p≥10)","<0.001 (5≤-log10p<10)","<0.01 (2≤-log10p<5)","Not Applicable","ns (p≥0.01)"))
immCorSiglec15$sign <- factor(immCorSiglec15$sign, levels = c("pos","neg"))

p1 <- quickcor(t(immPath.score), 
         type = "lower",
         show.diag = TRUE) + 
  geom_colour() +
  add_link(df = immCorSiglec15, 
           mapping = aes(colour = pSeg, size = rSeg, linetype = sign),
           spec.key = "gene",
           env.key = "path",
           diag.label = FALSE) +
  scale_size_manual(values = c(0.5, 1, 1.5, 2)) +
  scale_color_manual(values = c("#19A078","#DA6003","#7570B4","#E8288E","#65A818")) +
  scale_fill_gradient2(low = "#9483E1",mid = "white",high = "#E11953",midpoint=0) +
  remove_axis("x")
p1

ggsave(filename = "ggcor plot in bottom left.pdf", width = 10,height = 8)
